view.name: Washington State Cities and Counties
view.description: This dataset contains FIPS (Federal Information Processing Standard), GNIS (Geographic Name Information System common) codes for identifying Washington state counties cities and towns. This is an official list from OFM (Office of Financial Management).

columns.name: COUNTY FIPS CODE
columns.description: Federal Information Processing Standard code for WA State Counties

columns.name: CITY FIPS CODE
columns.description: Federal Information Processing Standard code for WA State Cities (Census 2000 & 2010)

columns.name: CITY FIPS CODE 90
columns.description: Federal Information Processing Standard code for Washington places (Census 1990). Note: The Census Bureau no longer maintains 1990 place codes. OFM assigned codes for cities which incorporated after 1999 for internal purposes.

columns.name: GNIS CODE
columns.description: Geographic Name Information System codes for WA State Counties (Note: GNIS codes are maintained by the U.S. Geological Survey http://geonames.usgs.gov/domestic/download_data.htm)

columns.name: MULTI-COUNTY FLAG
columns.description: Indicates if a city is located in more than one county
